# powerbi-project
KPI Essentials for Monitoring Amazon Sales Performance 

 YTD Sales: Continuously monitor year-to-date sales to evaluate overall revenue trends and long-term growth.
 QTD Sales: Track quarterly sales to identify seasonal trends and fluctuations that inform agile business adjustments.
 YTD Products Sold: Analyze the total number of products sold year-to-date to gain insight into product
 demand and movement.
 YTD Reviews: Keep an eye on year-to-date product reviews to understand customer feedback and
 satisfaction, helping to align product offerings with consumer expectations.
Charting Requirements for Comprehensive Sales Analysis 

 To deliver insightful visualizations for sales analytics, consider these chart types:

 YTD Sales by Month (Line Chart): Essential for visualizing monthly sales trends,
 identifying seasonal patterns, and understanding long-term growth trajectories.
 YTD Sales by Week (Column Chart): Provides weekly sales data to reveal short-term
 fluctuations and performance insights.
 Sales by Product Category (Text/Heat Map): Utilize this to display an overview of sales
 across various product categories, offering an at-a-glance view of top-performing
 segments.
 Top 5 Products by YTD Sales (Bar Chart): Highlights the leading products driving
 revenue, guiding strategic focus on key revenue generators.
 Top 5 Products by YTD Reviews (Bar Chart): Shows the most reviewed products to
 help gauge customer preferences and satisfaction
